## Section 7: Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|------|----------|------------|
| Existing `synthetic_lethality/` in crispro-v2 has a different model contract than our `ReceiptCandidate` | HIGH | Audit existing `models.py` before Day 1 ends. Write adapter layer to translate. Do not delete existing module until adapter is proven. |
| SQLite to Supabase migration breaks immutability guard timing | HIGH | Guards are in Python, not SQL. They fire before any DB write. DB-agnostic. |
| DepMap download (500MB) times out on Railway/Render cold start | MEDIUM | Pre-bake 36-gene DDR panel as static JSON. Add `pyarrow` to requirements. |
| GDSC parquet format requires pyarrow — missing from `requirements.txt` | MEDIUM | Add `pyarrow>=14.0` to `requirements.txt` immediately. |
| HIPAA/PII middleware in crispro-v2 strips fields we need | LOW | RUO tagging already on all responses. `audit_queue` stores no PHI. |
| Existing `doctor_portal.py` has its own `/coverage` endpoint that conflicts | LOW | Prefix our routes as `/api/v1/sl/audit/*` to avoid namespace collision. |
| Concurrent mine runs overwhelm DepMap matrix in memory | LOW | Matrix is read-only after load. Thread-safe. No mutex needed. |

